						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Vijayanagara Vīra-Harihararāya-Uḍaiyar, Śaka 1334 [in Kaṭapayādi system], Nandana, Aippasi 25 = 1412, October 23.</hi></p>						

						<p>Damaged. Gift of the village of Cheṅgaṟpaḷḷi in Kuṟuppu-nāḍu to the temple of Aṇiyādaḻagiyār at Vijaiyamangalam in Kuṟuppu-nāḍu for services and renovation. The gift was made jointly by the <hi rend="italic">nāṭṭavar</hi> of Vaḍa-parichār-nāḍu, Vengarai-nāḍu, Nālūr-paṟṟu, Pērūr-nāḍu, Kuṟuppu-nāḍu, and Vīrachōḻa-vaḷanāḍu included in Kōṭṭai <hi rend="italic">(kōṭṭaichūḻnda).</hi> </p>						

						</summary>
